/******************************************************************************************
 *
 *  BasiraGlasses.ino  —  Firmware v3.3.0
 *  BASIRA Smart Glasses — ESP32-C3 Super Mini
 *
 *  Hardware:
 *    TCRT5000   → GPIO0 (AO)
 *    Grove GSR  → GPIO2 (Analog)
 *    GL5528 LDR → GPIO3 (Analog)
 *    MAX30102   → GPIO8 (SDA), GPIO9 (SCL)
 *    Vibration  → GPIO10 (Digital Output)
 *
 * ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 *  ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS — v3.3 fixes (from serial log evidence)
 * ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 *
 *  FIX-1  BLINK RATE always 0.0 /min
 *  ─────────────────────────────────
 *  Root cause: Edge detection (OPEN→CLOSED, CLOSED→OPEN) was inside
 *  calculateBlinkFeatures() which runs every FEATURE_PERIOD = 1000ms.
 *  A full blink lasts 150–400ms. The 1000ms snapshot sees the eye in
 *  the same state as the previous second nearly every time — so the
 *  rising/falling edge is never captured and blinkCount stays 0.
 *
 *  Evidence: Serial log shows BLINK raw alternating 298/4095 correctly,
 *  but "Blink rate: 0.0 /min" persists for the entire session.
 *
 *  Fix: blinkCount++ logic moved entirely into readBlinkSensor() which
 *  runs every BLINK_PERIOD = 20ms. At 20ms resolution a 150ms blink is
 *  sampled ~7 times — the OPEN→CLOSED edge is reliably detected.
 *  calculateBlinkFeatures() now only handles the 30s window arithmetic,
 *  not edge detection.
 *
 *  FIX-2  GSR always 4095 — user instruction fix
 *  ───────────────────────────────────────────────
 *  Evidence from serial log: GSR raw=4095 throughout, even with ADC_11db.
 *  This is CORRECT hardware behavior — Grove GSR output is near VCC when
 *  no skin contact is made. The op-amp buffer in the Grove module pulls
 *  the output high when the electrode circuit is open.
 *
 *  The ADC_11db configuration IS working (confirmed: TCRT reads 297–343
 *  when closed, 4095 when open — correct 12-bit full-range behavior).
 *
 *  The user was testing WITHOUT placing both electrodes on skin.
 *  Fixes applied:
 *    a) analogSetPinAttenuation(PIN_GSR, ADC_11db) — explicit per-pin
 *       attenuation as a safeguard against Arduino core version differences.
 *    b) Serial calibration message now explicitly warns: attach both
 *       electrodes to index + middle finger BEFORE powering on.
 *    c) GSR_FLOATING_THRESHOLD lowered to 3800 — more conservative.
 *       At 3.3V / 12-bit: skin contact typically gives 1000–3000 ADC,
 *       floating/no-contact gives 3900–4095. 3800 gives a safety margin.
 *
 *  FIX-3  Light sensor restored to v3.0 behavior
 *  ───────────────────────────────────────────────
 *  Evidence: Light sensor was working correctly in v3.0/v3.1.
 *  The hysteresis from v3.2 (±10 count dead-band) is preserved as it
 *  prevents rapid state flipping, but the baseline and thresholds are
 *  restored. LIGHT_PERIOD remains 500ms as set in v3.2.
 *
 *  All v3.2 fixes preserved:
 *    - ADC 12-bit + ADC_11db configuration
 *    - TCRT averaging (8 samples), GSR averaging (10 samples)
 *    - PERCLOS live update every 1s (partial window)
 *    - RR interval bounds [300ms–1500ms] for HRV
 *    - BLE first packet fires immediately after calibration
 *
 ******************************************************************************************/

